  <original-body>In testing some functionality with transactions, I noticed that assert_queries works inconsistent with sqlite vs mysql.

A sqlite transaction would produce 1 query and mysql 3, because mysql uses the BEGIN and COMMIT keywords. This patch removes those keywords from the queries before comparing.

Note: Other db's might need similar adjustment, but these are my database flavours.</original-body>
